<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
The first record of this species from Korea is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim, CW" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" refId="B32" refString="Kim, CW, 1971. Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643-678, 758-824." title="Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643 - 678, 758 - 824." year="1971">Kim (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, no information was listed on which specimen(s) that record had been made, but the illustration (fig. 36) shows a species which is different from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. lygropis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lygropis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">H. lygropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 54–58" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figures 54 - 58. Hexatoma (Eriocera) lygropis (Alexander, 1920) 54 male, dorsal view 55 erroneous image of H. lygropis on which were based all Korean records 56 male wing 57 male genitalia, dorsal view 58 male genitalia with ninth segment removed, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (54, 56); 0.5 mm (57, 58). (55 after Kim (1971))." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1105.82495.figures54-58" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/700740" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">55</figureCitation>
). The most obvious difference is the missing cell m1, while 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. lygropis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lygropis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">H. lygropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a well-developed cell m1. The Korean University collection, on which 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim, CW" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" refId="B32" refString="Kim, CW, 1971. Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643-678, 758-824." title="Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643 - 678, 758 - 824." year="1971">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kim’s">Kim's</normalizedToken>
(1971)
</bibRefCitation>
publication was based, has a few 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Hexatoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexatoma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Hexatoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. lygropis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lygropis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">H. lygropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but all of them are in fact 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. pernigrina" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pernigrina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">H. pernigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which also has no cell m1. All other records of that species are based only on 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim, CW" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" refId="B32" refString="Kim, CW, 1971. Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643-678, 758-824." title="Family 1. Blepharoceridae - Family 11. Cecidomyiidae; Family 13. Xylophagidae - Family 24. Dolichopodidae. Illustrated encyclopedia of fauna and flora of Korea, 12, Insecta 4: 643 - 678, 758 - 824." year="1971">Kim (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on this, we exclude 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. lygropis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lygropis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">H. lygropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Korean species list. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alexander" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Hexatoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexatoma lygropis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lygropis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Hexatoma lygropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Taiwan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
